OL,3,CCreeslough families call for public
OL,4,Cinquiry into explosion
OL,6,FThe letter written by Mr Mackin
OL,7,Fhighlighted that the families of the
OL,8,Fvictims had each endured "unimaginable
OL,9,Fpain and suffering".
OL,11,F"Their families remain unable to
OL,12,Fgrieve for their loss until such times
OL,13,Fas they know the truth of what
OL,14,Foccurred, the failings are
OL,15,Facknowledged, and specific lessons are
OL,16,Flearned so that an incident like this
OL,17,Fnever happens again," he wrote.
OL,19,FThe letter noted that the only current
OL,20,Fexamination of the incident is the
OL,21,Fcriminal investigation by gardai.
